OL,3,CHow ironstone mined from the Cleveland
OL,4,CHills helped build the world
OL,6,F"It was very hard, very dirty. The
OL,7,Fmines were always wet. They were
OL,8,Fworking by candlelight, and because
OL,9,Fthe miners had to buy their own
OL,10,Fcandles, they would work by one
OL,11,Fcandle. Blasting with black powder,
OL,12,Fgunpowder."
OL,14,FThe days of the industrial revolution
OL,15,Fare long gone, but Cleveland iron
OL,16,Fremains visible in all corners of the
OL,17,Fworld and a key part of the region's
OL,18,Fheritage.
